adjectives.description: unimpregnable (comparative more unimpregnable, superlative most unimpregnable)

entries.meaning: Not impregnable; capable of being pierced or assailed.
examples: Without being a coward, Jean's courage is not unimpregnable, and therefore plays he not the swaggerer amongst the patients.

entries.meaning: Incapable of being impregnated; impermeable or infertile.
examples: The compound rendered the surface of the vessel unimpregnable.
Despite fertility treatment, one out of three women in the study remained unimpregnable.
